        <workgroup>EPITECH</workgroup>
        <keyword>R-Type</keyword>
    </front>

    <middle>
        <section anchor="intro" title="Introduction">

            <t>The R-Type is a third year project at EPITECH school. The objective of this project is to implement a
                multiplayer R-Type game from 1 to 4 players, using a client/server architecture.
            </t>

            <t>Here is the protocol we have wrote to describe how clients and server exchange data trough
                network.
                This paper assumes knowledge of the User Datagram Protocol
                <eref target="https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc768">(UDP)</eref>
            </t>

            <section title="Terminology">
                <t>The key words "MUST", "MUST NOT", "REQUIRED", "SHALL", "SHALL
                    NOT", "SHOULD", "SHOULD NOT", "RECOMMENDED", "MAY", and "OPTIONAL"
                    in this document are to be interpreted as described in
                    <xref target="RFC2119"/>.
                </t>
            </section>
        </section>

        <section anchor="protocol" title="The R-Type Protocol">

            <t>
                The protocol will use UDP to communicate between client and server,
                every packet that the client receive that does not come from the server will be ignored.
                The same happen for the server, every packet not recognized by the server won't be taken into
                consideration.
            </t>

            <figure>
                <artwork>
                             UDP transmission
+--------------+            +------------+            +-------------+
|    Client    |------------|   Server   |------------|    Client   |
+--------------+            +------------+            +-------------+
                </artwork>
            </figure>
        </section>

        <section title="Protocol">
            <t>
                Operation codes are on 3 bytes
                <list>
                    <t>1XX - Used for out of game protocol</t>
                    <t>2XX - Used for in-game protocol</t>
                    <t>3XX - Used for errors</t>
                </list>
            </t>

            <section title="Out of game protocol">
                <t>
                    <list>
                        <t>10X - Connection</t>
                        <t>11X - Rooms</t>
                    </list>
                </t>
            </section>

            <section title="In-game protocol">
                <t>
                    <list>
                        <t>200 - Action</t>
                        <t>210 - Disp</t>
                        <t>220 - Living</t>
                        <t>230 - Charge</t>
                        <t>240 - Score</t>
                        <t>250 - EndGame</t>
                    </list>
                </t>
            </section>

            <section title="Errors">
                <t>
                    <list>
                        <t>30X - Error</t>
                    </list>
                </t>
            </section>
        </section>

        <section title="Packets">
            <section anchor="connection" title="Connection">
                <t>
                    These packets are used to describe the connection steps.
                </t>

                <section anchor="connect" title="Connect">
                    <t>
                        100 : Connect : X bytes
                        <vspace blankLines="2"/>
                        This packet is sent continuously by the client until a
                        <xref target="connected"/>
                        packet has been received.
                    </t>

                    <texttable>
                        <preamble>Connection packet</preamble>
                        <ttcol align="center">OpCode</ttcol>
                        <ttcol align="center" width="75%">Username</ttcol>

                        <c>3 bytes</c>
                        <c>10 bytes</c>
                    </texttable>
                </section>

                <section anchor="connected" title="Connected">
                    <t>
                        101 : Connected : X bytes
                        <vspace blankLines="2"/>
                        This packet is sent continuously by the server when he received a connect packet (<xref
                            target="connect"/>). It stops when the server receive a pong packet (<xref target="pong"/>).
                    </t>

                    <texttable>
                        <preamble>Connection packet</preamble>
                        <ttcol align="center">OpCode</ttcol>

                        <c>3 bytes</c>
                    </texttable>
                </section>

                <section anchor="ping" title="Ping">
                    <t>
                        102 : Ping : X bytes
                        <vspace blankLines="2"/>
                        This packet is used to check the availability of a connected client or server. The response of
                        this packet is always a pong packet (<xref target="pong"/>).
                    </t>

                    <texttable>
                        <preamble>Ping packet</preamble>
                        <ttcol align="center">OpCode</ttcol>

                        <c>3 bytes</c>
                    </texttable>
                </section>

                <section anchor="pong" title="Pong">
                    <t>
                        103 : Pong : X bytes
                        <vspace blankLines="2"/>
                        This packet is the response of a ping packet (<xref target="ping"/>).
                    </t>

                    <texttable>
                        <preamble>Ping packet</preamble>
                        <ttcol align="center">OpCode</ttcol>

                        <c>3 bytes</c>
                    </texttable>
                </section>

                <section anchor="disconnect" title="Disconnect">
                    <t>
                        104 : Disconnect : X bytes
                        <vspace blankLines="2"/>
                        This packet informs the client that the server is going to shutdown or the server that the client is disconnecting.
                    </t>

                    <texttable>
                        <preamble>Disconnect</preamble>
                        <ttcol align="center">OpCode</ttcol>

                        <c>3 bytes</c>
                    </texttable>
                </section>

                <section anchor="Disconnected" title="Disconnected">
                    <t>
                        105 : Disconnected : X bytes
                        <vspace blankLines="2"/>
                        This packet is send as response to disconnect packet (<xref target="disconnect"/>) to confirm the reception of disconnection.
                    </t>

                    <texttable>
                        <preamble>Disconnected</preamble>
                        <ttcol align="center">OpCode</ttcol>

                        <c>3 bytes</c>
                    </texttable>
                </section>
            </section>

            <section anchor="rooms" title="Rooms">
                <t>
                    These packets are used to describe the room system.
                </t>

                <section anchor="get-rooms" title="Get rooms">
                    <t>
                        110 : Get rooms : X bytes
                        <vspace blankLines="2"/>
                        This packet is sent continuously by the client until it receives a list
                        of rooms packet (<xref target="rooms-list"/>)
                    </t>

                    <texttable>
                        <preamble>Get rooms</preamble>
                        <ttcol align="center">OpCode</ttcol>

                        <c>3 bytes</c>
                    </texttable>
                </section>

                <section anchor="rooms-list" title="Rooms list">
                    <t>
                        111 : Rooms list : X bytes
                        <vspace blankLines="2"/>
                    </t>

                    <texttable>
                        <preamble>Rooms</preamble>
                        <ttcol align="center">OpCode</ttcol>
                        <ttcol align="center">Rooms count</ttcol>
                        <ttcol align="center">Room name</ttcol>
                        <ttcol align="center">Require password</ttcol>
                        <ttcol align="center">Slots used</ttcol>
                        <ttcol align="center">Capacity</ttcol>

                        <c>3 bytes</c>
                        <c>4 bytes</c>
                        <c>10 bytes</c>
                        <c>1 bytes</c>
                        <c>1 bytes</c>
                        <c>1 bytes</c>
                    </texttable>
                </section>

                <section anchor="create-room" title="Create rooms">
                    <t>
                        112 : Create room : X bytes
                        <vspace blankLines="2"/>
                    </t>

                    <texttable>
                        <preamble>Create rooms</preamble>
                        <ttcol align="center">OpCode</ttcol>
                        <ttcol align="center">Room name</ttcol>
                        <ttcol align="center">Capacity</ttcol>
                        <ttcol align="center">Password size</ttcol>
                        <ttcol align="center">Password</ttcol>

                        <c>3 bytes</c>
                        <c>10 bytes</c>
                        <c>1 bytes</c>
                        <c>4 bytes</c>
                        <c>&lt;Password size> bytes</c>
                    </texttable>
                </section>

                <section anchor="ok-create" title="OK create room">
                    <t>
                        113 : OK create : X bytes
                        <vspace blankLines="2"/>
                        This packet is sent as response to a create room packet (<xref target="create-room"/>)
                    </t>

                    <texttable>
                        <preamble>Ok create</preamble>
                        <ttcol align="center">OpCode</ttcol>

                        <c>3 bytes</c>
                    </texttable>
                </section>

                <section anchor="quit-room" title="Quit room">
                    <t>
                        114 : Quit room : X bytes
                        <vspace blankLines="2"/>
                        This packet is sent continuously by the client that wants to leave a room
                        until it receives a ok quit packet (<xref target="ok-quit"/>)
                    </t>

                    <texttable>
                        <preamble>Quit room</preamble>
                        <ttcol align="center">OpCode</ttcol>

                        <c>3 bytes</c>
                    </texttable>
                </section>

                <section anchor="ok-quit" title="OK quit room">
                    <t>
                        115 : OK quit : X bytes
                        <vspace blankLines="2"/>
                        This packet is sent as response to a quit room packet (<xref target="quit-room"/>)
                    </t>

                    <texttable>
                        <preamble>Ok quit</preamble>
                        <ttcol align="center">OpCode</ttcol>

                        <c>3 bytes</c>
                    </texttable>
                </section>

                <section anchor="join-room" title="Join room">
                    <t>
                        116 : Join room : X bytes
                        <vspace blankLines="2"/>
                    </t>

                    <texttable>
                        <preamble>Join room</preamble>
                        <ttcol align="center">OpCode</ttcol>
                        <ttcol align="center">Room name</ttcol>
                        <ttcol align="center">Password size</ttcol>
                        <ttcol align="center">Password</ttcol>

                        <c>3 bytes</c>
                        <c>10 bytes</c>
                        <c>4 bytes</c>
                        <c>&lt;Password size> bytes</c>
                    </texttable>
                </section>

                <section anchor="joined-room" title="Joined room">
                    <t>
                        117 : Joined room : X bytes
                        <vspace blankLines="2"/>
                    </t>

                    <texttable>
                        <preamble>Joined room</preamble>
                        <ttcol align="center">OpCode</ttcol>
                        <ttcol align="center">User count</ttcol>
                        <ttcol align="center">Username</ttcol>

                        <c>3 bytes</c>
                        <c>1 bytes</c>
                        <c>&lt;User count> * 10 bytes</c>
                    </texttable>
                </section>

            </section>

            <section anchor="in-game" title="In-game Packets">
                <t>
                    These packets are send during the game to describe actions made by the client or
                    informations about the game being played.
                </t>

                <section anchor="action" title="Action">
                    <t>
                        200 : Action : X bytes
                        <vspace blankLines="2"/>
                        This packet contains a boolean for every key of a client. The boolean is true if the key is pressed
                    </t>

                    <texttable>
                        <preamble>Action</preamble>
                        <ttcol align="center">OpCode</ttcol>
                        <ttcol align="center">Shot</ttcol>
                        <ttcol align="center">Up</ttcol>
                        <ttcol align="center">Down</ttcol>
                        <ttcol align="center">Left</ttcol>
                        <ttcol align="center">Right</ttcol>

                        <c>3 bytes</c>
                        <c>1 bytes</c>
                        <c>1 bytes</c>
                        <c>1 bytes</c>
                        <c>1 bytes</c>
                        <c>1 bytes</c>
                    </texttable>
                </section>

                <section anchor="disp" title="Display entity">
                    <t>
                        210 : Disp : X bytes
                        <vspace blankLines="2"/>
                        This packet contains minimal informations to let the client display an entity
                    </t>

                    <texttable>
                        <preamble>Disp</preamble>
                        <ttcol align="center">OpCode</ttcol>
                        <ttcol align="center">Entity ID</ttcol>
                        <ttcol align="center">Positions [X, Y, Z]</ttcol>
                        <ttcol align="center">Rotation [X, Y]</ttcol>
                        <ttcol align="center">Scale [X, Y]</ttcol>
                        <ttcol align="center">Type</ttcol>

                        <c>3 bytes</c>
                        <c>8 bytes</c>
                        <c>12 bytes</c>
                        <c>8 bytes</c>
                        <c>8 bytes</c>
                        <c>4 bytes</c>
                    </texttable>

                </section>

                <section anchor="living" title="Living">
                    <t>
                        220 : Living : X bytes
                        <vspace blankLines="2"/>
                        This packet contains the health points of an entity
                    </t>

                    <texttable>
                        <preamble>Living</preamble>
                        <ttcol align="center">OpCode</ttcol>
                        <ttcol align="center">Entity ID</ttcol>
                        <ttcol align="center">HP</ttcol>

                        <c>3 bytes</c>
                        <c>8 bytes</c>
                        <c>4 bytes</c>
                    </texttable>
                </section>

                <section anchor="charge" title="Charge">
                    <t>
                        230 : Charge : X bytes
                        <vspace blankLines="2"/>
                        This packet contains the charge percentage of the player
                    </t>

                    <texttable>
                        <preamble>Living</preamble>
                        <ttcol align="center">OpCode</ttcol>
                        <ttcol align="center">Charge percentage</ttcol>

                        <c>3 bytes</c>
                        <c>1 bytes</c>
                    </texttable>
                </section>

                <section anchor="score" title="Score">
                    <t>
                        240 : Score : X bytes
                        <vspace blankLines="2"/>
                        This packet contains the score of the players.
                    </t>

                    <texttable>
                        <preamble>Living</preamble>
                        <ttcol align="center">OpCode</ttcol>
                        <ttcol align="center">Player 1</ttcol>
                        <ttcol align="center">Player 2</ttcol>
                        <ttcol align="center">Player 3</ttcol>
                        <ttcol align="center">Player 4</ttcol>

                        <c>3 bytes</c>
                        <c>1 bytes</c>
                        <c>1 bytes</c>
                        <c>1 bytes</c>
                    </texttable>
                </section>

                <section anchor="end-game" title="Endgame">
                    <t>
                        240 : Endgame : X bytes
                        <vspace blankLines="2"/>
                        This packet contains the score of the players and informs the client that the game has ended.
                    </t>

                    <texttable>
                        <preamble>Endgame</preamble>
                        <ttcol align="center">OpCode</ttcol>
                        <ttcol align="center">Player 1</ttcol>
                        <ttcol align="center">Player 2</ttcol>
                        <ttcol align="center">Player 3</ttcol>
                        <ttcol align="center">Player 4</ttcol>

                        <c>3 bytes</c>
                        <c>1 bytes</c>
                        <c>1 bytes</c>
                        <c>1 bytes</c>
                    </texttable>
                </section>
            </section>

            <section anchor="errors" title="Errors">
                <t>
                    These packets are used to describe all the errors that may occur.
                </t>

                <section anchor="unknown" title="Unknown packet">
                    <t>
                        300 : Unknown packet : X bytes
                        <vspace blankLines="2"/>
                        This packet is sent as response to any unknown packet.
                    </t>

                    <texttable>
                        <preamble>Unknown packet</preamble>
                        <ttcol align="center">OpCode</ttcol>

                        <c>3 bytes</c>
                    </texttable>
                </section>

                <section anchor="invalid" title="Invalid packet">
                    <t>
                        301 : Invalid packet : X bytes
                        <vspace blankLines="2"/>
                        This packet is sent as response to any packet that has a known opcode but has malformated data.
                    </t>

                    <texttable>
                        <preamble>Invalid packet</preamble>
                        <ttcol align="center">OpCode</ttcol>

                        <c>3 bytes</c>
                    </texttable>
                </section>

                <section anchor="invalid-param" title="Invalid param">
                    <t>
                        302 : Invalid param : X bytes
                        <vspace blankLines="2"/>
                        This packet is sent as response to any packet that is well formatted but has an invalid param.
                    </t>

                    <texttable>
                        <preamble>Invalid param</preamble>
                        <ttcol align="center">OpCode</ttcol>

                        <c>3 bytes</c>
                    </texttable>
                </section>

                <section anchor="duplicated-username" title="Already used username">
                    <t>
                        302 : Already used username : X bytes
                        <vspace blankLines="2"/>
                        This packet is sent as response to a connect packet (<xref target="connect"/>) when the username
                        requested is already used by another client.
                    </t>

                    <texttable>
                        <preamble>Already used username</preamble>
                        <ttcol align="center">OpCode</ttcol>

                        <c>3 bytes</c>
                    </texttable>
                </section>

                <section anchor="duplicated-room" title="Room name already used">
                    <t>
                        303 : Room name already used : X bytes
                        <vspace blankLines="2"/>
                        This packet is sent as response to a create room packet (<xref target="create-room"/>) when a
                        room exists with the same name.
                    </t>

                    <texttable>
                        <preamble>Room name already used</preamble>
                        <ttcol align="center">OpCode</ttcol>

                        <c>3 bytes</c>
                    </texttable>
                </section>

                <section anchor="not-in-room" title="Not in room">
                    <t>
                        304 : Not in room : X bytes
                        <vspace blankLines="2"/>
                        This packet is sent as response to a quit room packet (<xref target="quit-room"/>) when the
                        client isn't in any room.
                    </t>

                    <texttable>
                        <preamble>Not in room</preamble>
                        <ttcol align="center">OpCode</ttcol>

                        <c>3 bytes</c>
                    </texttable>
                </section>

                <section anchor="room-not-exist" title="Unknown room">
                    <t>
                        305 : Unknown room : X bytes
                        <vspace blankLines="2"/>
                        This packet is sent as response to a join room packet (<xref target="join-room"/>) when the room
                        name request is unknown.
                    </t>

                    <texttable>
                        <preamble>Unknown room</preamble>
                        <ttcol align="center">OpCode</ttcol>

                        <c>3 bytes</c>
                    </texttable>
                </section>

                <section anchor="invalid-password" title="Invalid password">
                    <t>
                        306 : Invalid password : X bytes
                        <vspace blankLines="2"/>
                        This packet is sent as response to a join room packet (<xref target="join-room"/>) when the
                        password is invalid.
                    </t>

                    <texttable>
                        <preamble>invalid password</preamble>
                        <ttcol align="center">OpCode</ttcol>

                        <c>3 bytes</c>
                    </texttable>
                </section>

                <section anchor="room-full" title="Room full">
                    <t>
                        307 : Room full : X bytes
                        <vspace blankLines="2"/>
                        This packet is sent as response to a join room packet (<xref target="join-room"/>) when the room
                        has no empty slots.
                    </t>

                    <texttable>
                        <preamble>Room full</preamble>
                        <ttcol align="center">OpCode</ttcol>

                        <c>3 bytes</c>
                    </texttable>
                </section>
            </section>
        </section>
    </middle>

